<br>
I tested two combos out using a parser.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind, my weapon and hand to hand are all maxed.  I was solo, no buffs influenced any part of my attacking.<br>
<br>
My haste is Cloak of Flames, and did not change through the test.<br>
<br>
Here's the results:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> **Celestial fists combo #1: Bare fist primary + Staff of shielding Secondary<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> o o o total # of mobs killed: 36<br>
o o o average damage per second: 69.3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> **Celestial fists combo #2: Tranquil Staff<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> o o o total # of mobs killed: 21 (was getting sleepy =P)<br>
o o o average damage per second: 74.2 (not including procs)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
doing just a plain old t-test on the data, they are significantly different.  I can say with 95% confidence that TS is better than h2h + SoS, at least at level 56.  It will be interesting to see what effect level has on things.<br>
<br>
the most significant part of this, of course, is that the TS data did not include non-melee damage done, which averaged 1.6 procs per kill.  this is an extra 3.8 damage per second, not to mention the variable stun factor.  This brings the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> TS combo up to 78.0 damage per second</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, further increasing the significance of the difference (p&lt;0.01)<br>
<br>
i'll keep you guys updated as i level.  but after arguing with many monks who insist h2h/SoS is better, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> i can now conclusively say it isn't.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
of course, there is the issue of AC, but in most group situations, having a slower weapon like TS will keep agro off you.  I find agro is -higher- with h2h/s0s, most likely negating the AC difference in a group.  <br>
<br>
